    "discriminators": [
     "Loud, LOW, steady and harmonically dense: a pressure-driven diaphragm or reed blaring on a fixed pitch. Flat sustain, low crest_factor, a deep partial comb, and real low_band_energy.",
     "The pitch axis separates HORNS from WHISTLES cleanly: a horn is low with many partials, a whistle is high (1-4 kHz) with almost none. Do not confuse them.",
     "ALARMS-SIREN sweeps and this does not — a horn holds one pitch for the length of the blast.",
     "Machine-driven, so the onset is fast and the sustain is rock steady, unlike the breathy human-blown HORNS-TRADITIONAL.",
     "Ship and ferry horns go to BOATS-HORN, locomotive horns to TRAINS-HORN and car horns to VEHICLES-HORN even though the physics is identical. Only the source word in the name can make that split."
    ],
