    "discriminators": [
     "A buzzed reed or buzzed lip: strongly harmonic, mid-pitched, and DIRTY — high total_harmonic_distortion with a dense partial comb. A vuvuzela is a sustained droning buzz; a party horn is a short squawk with the same timbre.",
     "Higher-pitched and much shorter than HORNS-AIR POWERED, which is a low, very loud, sustained blast.",
     "The fanfare, bugle and trumpet synonyms pull toward MUSICAL-BRASS. A performed brass line belongs there; a single celebratory toot belongs here, and only the name can tell them apart."
    ],
