    "discriminators": [
     "Human-blown natural horn — shofar, conch, alpenhorn, battle horn. The tell is the BREATH: a noticeably slower attack and an unstable, wavering sustain, with audible breath noise lifting spectral_flatness above what a machine horn shows.",
     "HORNS-AIR POWERED is machine-driven: instant onset, rock-steady sustain, far more power, cleaner spectrum. That onset/stability contrast is the only real signal-side split between the two.",
     "Bugle overlaps HORNS-CELEBRATION and MUSICAL-BRASS; the words shofar, conch, alphorn, war and battle are what pin a file here."
    ],
